  "text": "Various kinds of curve plots have also been used in other visualization systems as a selection tool [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , so we will first describe the construction of a typical pathline plot. Let L = {l 1 , l 2 ,...l n } be the set of trajectories and X = {x 1 , x 2 ,...x m } be the attributes associated with each trajectory. Let the function f i (x j ,t) be the value of x j on trajectory l i at time t. The user selects two arbitrary attributes x j and x k to create a curve plot. For each trajectory l i , an attribute curve is generated on a XY coordinate plane by plotting every data point",
